(244, 4, '2016-09-08 08:27:53', '2016-09-08 08:27:53', 'You can do this in two ways to trigger a click event in javascript:\r\n\r\n<b><u>Javascript:</u></b>\r\n<i>By calling the function as an attribute</i><u>:</u>\r\n<code class="prettyprint inline prettyprinted"><span class="tag">&lt;button</span> <span class="atn">id</span><span class="pun">=</span><span class="atv">"myButton"</span> <span class="atn">onclick</span><span class="pun">=</span><span class="atv">"</span><span class="pln">doSomething</span><span class="pun">()</span><span class="atv">"</span><span class="tag">&gt;</span><span class="pln">Submit</span><span class="tag">&lt;/button&gt;</span></code>\r\n\r\n<i>By attaching to the click event of the button</i><u>:</u>\r\n<ol class="linenums">\r\n 	<li class="L0"><span class="kwd">var</span><span class="pln"> button </span><span class="pun">=</span><span class="pln"> document</span><span class="pun">.</span><span class="pln">getElementById</span><span class="pun">(</span><span class="str">"myButton"</span><span class="pun">);</span></li>\r\n 	<li class="L1"><span class="pln">button</span><span class="pun">.</span><span class="pln">addEventListener</span><span class="pun">(</span><span class="str">"click"</span><span class="pun">,</span><span class="pln"> doSomething</span><span class="pun">);</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nPS: In both cases, you will need to have Javascript function called <i>doSomething</i> defined someplace in your document.\r\n\r\n<b><u>jQuery:</u></b>\r\n<ol class="linenums">\r\n 	<li class="L0"><span class="pln">$</span><span class="pun">(</span><span class="kwd">function</span><span class="pun">(){</span></li>\r\n 	<li class="L1"><span class="pln"> $</span><span class="pun">(</span><span class="str">''#myButton''</span><span class="pun">).</span><span class="pln">on</span><span class="pun">(</span><span class="str">''click''</span><span class="pun">,</span> <span class="kwd">function</span><span class="pun">(</span><span class="pln">e</span><span class="pun">){</span></li>\r\n 	<li class="L2"><span class="com">// handle click event of button</span></li>\r\n 	<li class="L3"><span class="pun">});</span></li>\r\n 	<li class="L4"><span class="pun">});</span></li>\r\n</ol>', 'Trigger a click event in javascript or Jquery', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'trigger-a-click-event-in-javascript', '', '', '2016-09-08 08:29:07', '2016-09-08 08:29:07', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wptestsite/?p=244', 0, 'post', '', 0);
