(248, 4, '2016-09-08 08:53:06', '2016-09-08 08:53:06', '<h2>Central Processing Unit contains:</h2>\r\nProgram Control unit or instruction unit: Its function is the fetch instruction from memory.\r\n\r\nArithmetic logic Unit: It process or execute carried out instructions. Its called Arithmetic logic Unit because instructions specify either arithmetic (numeric) operations or non-numeric operations that is reasoning or decision making.\r\n\r\nMain Memory: Its purpose is to store active instructions and data.\r\n\r\nInput/Output equipment: To provide communication between a computers and its human users, a mean of translating information between human and machine (binary) formats is necessary. The input output equipment performs this tasks.\r\n\r\nData: Which is names and numbers. Ex. Student Name, Student ID. Instruction: For example, the instruction ADD 2000 3000 Contains the operation code/opcode ADD and operands 2000 and 3000.', 'Components of Machine computation and Human computation', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'components-human-computation-machine-computation', '', '', '2016-09-08 08:53:22', '2016-09-08 08:53:22', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wptestsite/?p=248', 0, 'post', '', 0),
