(250, 4, '2016-09-08 08:57:27', '2016-09-08 08:57:27', '&nbsp;\r\n<h2>A Turing Machine</h2>\r\nIn the 1930s the English mathematician Alan .M Turing (1912-54) introduced an abstract model of a computer called a Turing machine. The memory of a Turing machine is a tape M and is divided lengthwise into squares. The Turing machines processor P is linked to M by a read-write head that can write into or can read the contents of one square Q and move the tape one to the left or right of the current square Q.', 'A Turing Machine', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-turing-machine', '', '', '2016-09-08 09:00:12', '2016-09-08 09:00:12', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wptestsite/?p=250', 0, 'post', '', 0),
