ill change as\r\n items are removed) and removes the item if it''s found. It works in all browsers.\r\n\r\n\r\n</span></code></pre>\r\n<h1>*********************************************</h1>\r\n<h1>Useful Links</h1>\r\n<h2>Heap Useful Links</h2>\r\ni.<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binary_heap">Construction of a heap-01</a>\r\n\r\nii.<a href="https://www.tutorialspoint.com/data_structures_algorithms/heap_data_structure.htm">Construction of a heap-02</a>\r\n\r\niii.<a href="http://pages.cs.wisc.edu/~vernon/cs367/notes/11.PRIORITY-Q.html">Priority queue using heap</a>\r\n\r\niv.<a href="https://www.siggraph.org/education/materials/HyperGraph/video/mpeg/mpegfaq/huffman_tutorial.html">Huffman coding-01</a>\r\n\r\nv.<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Huffman_coding">Huffman coding-02</a>\r\n<h2>Graph Useful Links</h2>\r\ni.<a href="http://algorithms.tutorialhorizon.com/graph-representation-adjacency-matrix-and-adjacency-list/">Representation of graph (Adjacenry matrix / using class)</a>\r\n\r\nii.<a href="http://www.radford.edu/~nokie/classes/360/graphs-terms.html">Graph terminologies</a>\r\n\r\niii.<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dijkstra%27s_algorithm">Dijkstra algorithm-01</a>\r\n\r\niv.<a href="http://www.geeksforgeeks.org/greedy-algorithms-set-6-dijkstras-shortest-path-algorithm/">Dijkstra algorithm-02</a>\r\n\r\nv.<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minimum_spanning_tree">MST(Minimum Spanning Tree) algorithms-01</a>\r\n\r\nvi.<a href="https://www.hackerearth.com/practice/algorithms/graphs/minimum-spanning-tree/tutorial/">MST(Minimum Spanning Tree) algorithms-02</a>\r\n\r\nvii.<a href="http://www.geeksforgeeks.org/greedy-algorithms-set-2-kruskals-minimum-spanning-tree-mst/">Union-Find data structure for Kruskal''s algorithm-01</a>\r\n\r\nviii.<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kruskal%27s_algorithm">Union-Find data structure for Kruskal''s algorithm-02</a>\r\n\r\nix.<a href="http://codingrecipies.blogspot.com/2013/09/max-spacing-for-k-order-cluster.html">k-clustering for maximum spacing-01</a>\r\n\r\nx.<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maximum_spacing_estimation">k-clustering for maximum spacing-02</a>\r\n\r\nxi.<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cycle_graph">Cycle graph and bi-partite graph (Algorithms)-01</a>\r\n\r\nxii.<a href="http://mathworld.wolfram.com/BipartiteGraph.html">Cycle graph and bi-partite graph (Algorithms)-02</a>\r\n\r\nxiii.<a href="http://www.geeksforgeeks.org/fleurys-algorithm-for-printing-eulerian-path/">Euler path and Euler circuit, FLeury''s algorithm-01</a>\r\n\r\nxiv.<a href="http://study.com/academy/lesson/fleurys-algorithm-for-finding-an-euler-circuit.html">Euler path and Euler circuit, FLeury''s algorithm-02</a>\r\n\r\nxv.<a href="http://math.stackexchange.com/questions/986007/find-maximum-number-of-nodes-in-a-regular-graph-of-degree-4-and-diameter-2">Finding degree and diameter of a node-01</a>\r\n\r\nxvi.<a href="http://combinatoricswiki.org/wiki/The_Degree/Diameter_Problem">Finding degree and diameter of a node-02</a>\r\n<h1>*********************************************</h1>\r\n<pre class="default prettyprint prettyprinted"><code><span class="pun"></span></code></pre>', 'How to check out a remote Git branch?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-check-out-a-remote-git-branch', '', '', '2016-09-30 17:01:20', '2016-09-30 17:01:20', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wptestsite/?p=384', 0, 'post', '', 0);
