(387, 1, '2016-09-27 16:05:12', '2016-09-27 16:05:12', '<h2>remove a property from a JavaScript object</h2>\r\nSuppose you have an object that looks like this :\r\n<pre class="default prettyprint prettyprinted"><code><span class="kwd">var</span> <span class="typ">Hogwarts</span> <span class="pun">=</span> <span class="pun">{</span><span class="pln">\r\n    staff </span><span class="pun">:</span> <span class="pun">[</span>\r\n        <span class="str">''Argus Filch''</span><span class="pun">,</span>\r\n        <span class="str">''Filius Flitwick''</span><span class="pun">,</span>\r\n        <span class="str">''Gilderoy Lockhart''</span><span class="pun">,</span>\r\n        <span class="str">''Minerva McGonagall''</span><span class="pun">,</span>\r\n        <span class="str">''Poppy Pomfrey''</span><span class="pun">,</span>\r\n        <span class="pun">...</span>\r\n    <span class="pun">],</span><span class="pln">\r\n    students </span><span class="pun">:</span> <span class="pun">[</span>\r\n        <span class="str">''Hannah Abbott''</span><span class="pun">,</span>\r\n        <span class="str">''Katie Bell''</span><span class="pun">,</span>\r\n        <span class="str">''Susan Bones''</span><span class="pun">,</span>\r\n        <span class="str">''Terry Boot''</span><span class="pun">,</span>\r\n        <span class="str">''Lavender Brown''</span><span class="pun">,</span>\r\n        <span class="pun">...</span>\r\n    <span class="pun">]</span>\r\n<span class="pun">};</span></code></pre>\r\n<h3>Deleting an object property</h3>\r\nIf you want to use the entire <code>staff</code> array, the proper way to do this, would be to do this :\r\n<pre class="default prettyprint prettyprinted"><code><span class="kwd">delete</span> <span class="typ">Hogwarts</span><span class="pun">.</span><span class="pln">staff</span><span class="pun">;</span></code></pre>\r\nAlternatively, you could also do this :\r\n<pre class="default prettyprint prettyprinted"><code><span class="kwd">delete</span> <span class="typ">Hogwarts</span><span class="pun">[</span><span class="str">''staff''</span><span class="pun">];</span></code></pre>\r\nSimilarly, removing the entire students array would be done by calling <code>delete Hogwarts.students;</code> or<code>delete Hogwarts[''students''];</code>.\r\n<h3>Deleting an array index</h3>\r\nNow, if you want to remove a single staff member or student, the procedure is a bit different, because both properties are arrays themselves.\r\n\r\nIf you know the index of your staff member, you could simply do this :\r\n<pre class="default prettyprint prettyprinted"><code><span class="typ">Hogwarts</span><span class="pun">.</span><span class="pln">staff</span><span class="pun">.</span><span class="pln">splice</span><span class="pun">(</span><span class="lit">3</span><span class="pun">,</span> <span class="lit">1</span><span class="pun">);</span></code></pre>\r\nIf you do not know the index, you''ll also have to do an index seach :\r\n<pre class="default prettyprint prettyprinted"><code><span class="typ">Hogwarts</span><span class="pun">.</span><span class="pln">staff</span><span class="pun">.</span><span class="pln">splice</span><span class="pun">(</span><span class="typ">Hogwarts</span><span class="pun">.</span><span class="pln">staff</span><span class="pun">.</span><span class="pln">indexOf</span><span class="pun">(</span><span class="str">''Minerva McGonnagall''</span><span class="pun">)</span> <span class="pun">-</span> <span class="lit">1</span><span class="pun">,</span> <span class="lit">1</span><span class="pun">);</span></code></pre>', 'How to remove a property from a JavaScript object?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'remove-particular-element-array-javascript-2', '', '', '2016-09-27 16:05:12', '2016-09-27 16:05:12', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wptestsite/?p=387', 0, 'post', '', 0),
