hat specific foods should I be eating?</a></span>\r\n\r\n<span class="qlink_container"><a href="https://www.quora.com/How-do-I-decrease-my-fat-percentage-without-reducing-muscle-mass" target="_blank">How do I decrease my fat percentage without reducing muscle mass?</a></span>\r\n\r\n<span class="qlink_container"><a href="https://www.quora.com/How-can-I-gain-muscle-without-using-weights" target="_blank">How can I gain muscle without using weights?</a></span>\r\n\r\n<span class="qlink_container"><a href="https://www.quora.com/How-can-I-lose-weight-and-gain-muscle-without-much-money" target="_blank">How can I lose weight and gain muscle without much money?</a></span>\r\n\r\n<span class="qlink_container"><a href="https://www.quora.com/How-can-I-gain-muscle-on-a-low-protein-diet" target="_blank">How can I gain muscle on a low protein diet?</a></span>\r\n\r\nThere are a variety of scenarios already written about this topic, to a point where I don''t think it really needed to be asked (but especially not without any specifics on the situation).\r\n\r\nGenerally people who ask these questions are not already hulks, so the simplest answer for you is to start strength training hard and eating a lot of high quality food.\r\n\r\nYou need to stimulate muscle growth with some kind of load, then use food to help it rebuild. Keep doing that over time and you''ll gain muscle. If you don''t you''re either:\r\n\r\nA) Not eating enough <i>(typically this one...)</i>\r\nB) Not training well enough\r\n\r\nIf you''re still lost, buy the book, ''Mass Made Simple'' by Dan John.', 'Gain weight in a healhty way', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '435-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-08 07:42:39', '2016-10-08 07:42:39', '', 435, 'http://localhost/wptestsite/435-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(437, 4, '2016-10-08 07:45:16', '2016-10-08 07:45:16', 'Ways to keep heart, lungs and liver in good condition\r\n<h2>Follow this Tips this will definitely works for you:</h2>\r\no Dont smoke\r\no Maintain a healthy weight\r\no Exercise\r\no Eat a heart healthy diet\r\n\r\nDiet can be a major risk factor is the development of heart disease. Not only do certain types of food have negative effects on blood fats and blood pressure, eating too much or the wrong types of food can lead to excess weight.\r\n\r\n<b>A diet that is healthy for your heart should include:</b>\r\n\r\no Plenty of fruit and vegetables\r\no Whole grainsLow fat dairy\r\no Moderate alcohol intake\r\nSource : <span class="qlink_container"><a class="external_link" href="http://www.doctorbing.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" data-qt-tooltip="doctorbing.com">www.doctorbing.com</a></span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Ways to keep heart, lungs and liver in good condition', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ways-keep-heart-lungs-liver-good-condition', '', '', '2016-10-08 07:45:16', '2016-10-08 07:45:16', '', 0, 'http://localhost/wptestsite/?p=437', 0, 'post', '', 0),
